CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 28, 1941, pg. 3, reads: "Kay Club Celebrates Ten Years Of Progress - The Kay Boys' Club of Pittsburgh is one of the city's outstanding social agencies.  Hundreds of boys are shown the right road to travel under capable supervision at the club and later become model citizens.  The Kay Club is doing much to encourage good citizenship and patriotism. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Exterior of Kay Boys' Club, with sign in window advertising "$100 in Prizes," 2038 Bedford Avenue at Seal Street, Hill District
